snippet.textDisplay: DHop said things are being blown way out of proportion. Have to take him at his word but still realize that they did trade him. O'Brien, just on his merits as a coach, has had puh-lenty of chances at Houston and has proven he can't really game plan or game manage at a level needed to win the big one. Texans have been very injury prone and very thin at key positions for years with a lot of that resulting from very poor general managers going all the way back to Charley Casserly. The line between winning a SB and just making it to the playoffs is pretty thin and you have to put up with some drama in order to get over the hump. Maybe O'Brien wants the receivers to do things that DHop is talking them out of or whatever but you sometimes gotta suck it up and let your stars lead the team. At the end of the day maybe this will be the impetus to getting rid of O'Brien. There are a lot of coaches who could do what he's done. Texans need to go get Urban Meyer or someone with some new ideas.
